To call a function multiple times in JavaScript, you can use a loop. Here's an example of how you can call a function 9 times using a `for` loop:

```javascript
function myFunction() {
  // code to be executed
}

for (let i = 0; i < 9; i++) {
  myFunction();
}
```

In the above code, the function `myFunction` will be called 9 times. You can replace `myFunction` with the name of the function you want to call.

